'''Nonkululeko Gobodo''' (born 10 October 1960, [[Mthatha]], Eastern Cape) became the first black female [[Chartered_accountant#South_Africa|Chartered Accountant in South Africa]] in 1987.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nonkululeko Gobodo|url=http://whoswho.co.za/nonkululeko-gobodo-3947|publisher=Who's Who Southern Africa|accessdate=10 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Cover Story: Winning Women: Nonkululeko Gobodo CA(SA)|url=http://www.accountancysa.org.za/cover-story-winning-women-nonkululeko-gobodo-casa/|accessdate=10 September 2016|work=Accountancy SA|date=1 November 2013}}</ref>
She founded the accountancy firm '''Gobodo Incorporated''' which in 2011 merged with [[SizweNtsaluba VSP]] to form [[SizweNtsalubaGobodo]], South Africa's largest black-owned accountancy firm. In 2014 she stepped down from the role of executive chair of the company.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ndzamela|first1=Phakamisa|title=SizweNtsalubaGobodo founder leaves|url=http://www.bdlive.co.za/business/financial/2014/10/27/sizwentsalubagobodo-founder-leaves|accessdate=10 September 2016|work=Business Day Live|date=27 October 2014}}</ref>
