{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Soren Schroder | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = Søren Wølck Schrøder<ref name=Bindslev2015>{{cite news |author1=Bindslev, J.C. |author2=Westermann, C. |date=5 October 2015 |title='Ukendt' dansker til tops i udlandet: Er han verdens bedst betalte dansker? | url=http://nyheder.tv2.dk/finans/2015-10-05-ukendt-dansker-til-tops-i-udlandet-er-han-verdens-bedst-betalte-dansker | language= Danish | publisher=[[TV 2 (Denmark)|TV2 News]] | accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=vldk2017>{{cite news |date=24 March 2017 |title=Soren Schroder er en dansk stjerne i toppen af en af verdens største virksomheder | url=https://vl.dk/2017/03/soren-schroder-er-en-dansk-stjerne-i-toppen-af-en-af-verdens-stoerste-virksomheder/ | language= Danish | publisher=vl.dk | accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth based on age as of date |54|2017|06|12}}<ref name="bloomberg1" /> | birth_place = [[Aarhus]], Denmark<ref name=Bindslev2015/><ref name=vldk2017/> | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | nationality = Danish<ref>{{cite web |author= |date=7 February 2016 |title=Søren Wølck Schrøder | url=https://udvandrerne.dk/usa/job/soeren-woelck-schroeder/ | language= Danish | publisher=udvandrerne.dk | accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref> | residence = | education = | alma mater = [[Connecticut College]] | occupation = businessman | title = CEO, [[Bunge Limited]] | term = June 2013- | predecessor = [[Alberto Weisser]] | successor = | known for = | boards = | salary = $11,185,520 (2016)<ref name="bloomberg1" /> | networth = | spouse = | children = | parents = | relations = | website = }}
'''Søren Wølck Schrøder''' (born 1962/63) is a Danish businessman,<ref name=Bindslev2015/><ref name=vldk2017/> the CEO of [[Bunge Limited]], a global agribusiness and food company, since June 2013.<ref name="weforum1">{{cite web|url=https://www.weforum.org/people/soren-schroder/ |title=Soren Schroder &#124; World Economic Forum |publisher=Weforum.org |date= |accessdate=June 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Polansek|first1=Tom|title=Bunge boss of two years faces pressure to improve results|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-bunge-ceo-idUSKBN0N82JA20150417|website=Reuters|accessdate=12 June 2017|date=17 April 2015}}</ref>
==Early life== Søren Wølck Schrøder was born in Aarhus in Denmark, but moved to the United States to study at [[Connecticut College]], where he received a bachelor's degree in economics.<ref name=Bindslev2015/><ref name="bloomberg1">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=43880876&privcapId=687261 |title=Executive Profile: Soren W. Schroder |publisher=bloomberg |date= |accessdate=June 12, 2017}}</ref><ref name="weforum1"/>
==Career== After finishing his bachelor's degree, Schroder worked for [[ContiGroup Companies|Continental Grain]] for more for than ten years and then transferred to [[Cargill]] for a shorter period.<ref name=vldk2017/> From 1997 to 2000, Schroder was a board member of the Danish company [[Scanola]], but otherwise he has worked exclusively abroad.<ref name=Bindslev2015/>
He has worked for Bunge since 2000, initially as Protein Director at Bunge Global Markets.<ref name=Bindslev2015/><ref name="bloomberg1" /> From 2010 to 2013 he was CEO of Bunge North America.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bunge.com/who-we-are/management |title=Management |publisher=Bunge |date= |accessdate=June 12, 2017}}</ref> He became CEO of Bunge Limited in June 2013, succeeding [[Alberto Weisser]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Weiderman|first1=Greta|title=Bunge appoints Soren Schroder as CEO|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/stlouis/morning_call/2013/02/bunge-appoints-soren-schroder-as-ceo.html|website=www.bizjournals.com|publisher=St. Louis Business Journal|accessdate=12 June 2017|date=7 February 2013}}</ref>
